This paper is about functional verification of hardware systems, which falls under the category of electronic design automation (EDA). Therefore, cs.ET (Electronic Design Automation) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses simulation-based verification techniques, which involve generating random test stimuli, and this could be considered a machine learning problem. Hence, cs.LG (Machine Learning) is another likely sub-category. The paper also deals with generating solutions for large constraint sets, which is a problem in computational complexity theory, and could be categorized under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) or cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). Finally, the paper discusses Boolean constraints, which is a topic in theoretical computer science, and could be categorized under cs.CC (Computational Complexity).
